f(z)={z+i\over z-i}, \quad z\in\mathbb{C}\setminus\{i\}
a,b,c
f(z)=\frac{z+i}{z-i}=1+\frac{2i}{z-i}\implies f'(z)=-\frac{2i}{(z-i)^2}\neq 0\;\;,\;\;\forall z\in\Bbb C-\{i\}
\,z=x+iy\;,\;\;x,y\in\Bbb R\;,\;x>0\;
f(z)=1+\frac{2i}{z-i}=1+\frac{2i}{x+(y-1)i}=1+\frac{2(y-1)+2xi}{x^2+(y-1)^2}
\;\;
\,(f(z))\;\;
\,|z|=1\iff x^2+y^2=1\;
